Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of high-performance computing and grid computing for scientific simulations, specifically in the domain of weather forecasting. This falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) as well as Distributed Systems (cs.Distributed Systems). The paper also mentions the use of communication protocols and tools such as Globus Toolkit, which falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The development of the Nimble@ITCEcnoGrid framework also involves software engineering (cs.SE) and computer engineering (cs.CE).
